reviews.text: Very nice Chinese Food Restaurant.  Has good food and very nice view of Hong Kong.  Highly recommended to have lunch or dinner at this restaurant.
Nice view and amazing food. Little hard to find. It is located on the 10th floor.
I did not pay by myself so don’t know price, it seems expensive. However very delicious and good atmosphere. Staff service is also very good. If you care your important person, here is recommendable.

A Michelin Star restaurant with excellent food, service and a great view - No surprises there. The only surprise is the price is more reasonable than you'd think for such a complete dining experience.

Made a reservation but had to wait for 15 mins before is given a table. Reception told us the table number and had to walk in ourselves. Ask one of the staff where is table 133 (our table) and he was like “wtf”. He walked away and helped his colleague to place foods on another table. Plates on the table is dirty. The price mismatch the quality of the foods as well as the hygiene. Pretty bad experience from start to end.

reviews.text: 經理不老实，沒有說明蟹和龍虾多少錢一両便落单，結果 澳洲2斤半龙虾两味是3200元港幣，做法是龍蝦肉蒸蛋 ,虾头做伊麵。一隻星加坡胡椒炒蟹是1200元港幣， 味道不是很差，但絕对不值這個價錢! 另外，咕嚕肉太酸， 鹽焗雞得个鹹字……只有幾味招牌菜還可以... 其他菜色很一般……不推介……
食物ok值一星、但服務一般
